Data Scientist		1010data		New York, NY		<div class="rich-text" itemprop="description">1010data travels at the speed of thought to make Big Data discovery easy; we power sub second responses to analyses run on billions of rows of data.<br /><br />An essential tool to more than 750 of the world’s top retail, manufacturing, telecom, government and financial services enterprises including The New York Stock Exchange, Dollar General, P&amp;G, and RiteAid; 1010data is a highly differentiated product that is becoming the industry standard for Big Data Discovery and Data Sharing.<br /><br />We are seeking Data Scientists with solid programming skills to create large-scale analytical solutions to client-driven business problems. This includes designing high-performance databases and the corresponding operation and workflow processes.<br /><br />With more than 21 trillion rows of data in our private cloud, 1010data is designed to scale to the largest volumes of granular data, the most disparate and varied data sets, and the most complex advanced analytics. All while delivering lightning-quick system performance.<br /><br />With direct access to data you will solve analytical problems whose solutions have large business impact and evolve our product as we continue to change the rules of big data discovery.<br /><br />This requires experience of software development principles and statistical modelling techniques as well as adeptness in at least one statistical programming language, such as R or SAS. Additional experience in a specific programming language is not required; for us it is more significant that you are interested, willing and able to learn new languages quickly.<br />Data Scientists at 1010data are creative self-starters who are passionate about using technology to solve real world business problems and add substantial value to the company—we are looking for more people that fit this mold.<br /><br /><strong>Responsibilities: <br /></strong><ul><li>Trusted advisor on the implications of data for products, processes, and decisions. </li> <li>Analyze massive data sets and gain unique industry insight using the 1010data platform </li> <li>Support blue chip clients in the use of the 1010data system </li> <li>Map client business issues to many data sets including the clients own</li> <li>Contribute to the creation of analytical products that combine the 1010data platform and hosted datasets</li> <li>Support sales and marketing as needed<br /></li></ul><strong>Requirements<br /></strong>Education &amp; Experience<br /><ul><li>STEM Bachelor’s required, PhD preferred; strong background in vector/matrix arithmetic a plus </li> <li>1-3 years of experience in quantitative analysis (OR) relevant academic research experience building analytical products </li> <li>Experience with retail and credit card data or consumer shopping data a plus <br /></li></ul>Skills<br /><ul><li>Understanding of database structure, design, query languages (e.g. SQL)</li> <li>Experience with Functional programming languages or high-level programming language (e.g. JavaScript, APL, Python, Ruby)</li> <li>Ability to design solutions which serve the operational needs of varied businesses</li> <li>Comprehensive understanding of: fundamentals of mathematics, large data sets distributed systems, statistical concepts</li> <li>Ability to gather and assess client requirements<br /></li></ul>Personal Impact<br /><ul><li>Critical thinking and problem solving skills</li> <li>Ability to clearly and concisely communicate</li> <li>Ability to understand projects at a high level without losing sight of granular details when managing projects</li> <li>Ability to both work collaboratively and independently</li> <li>Ability to work under pressure and meet deadlines</li> <li>Positive, balanced, “roll up your sleeves” attitude</li> <li>Drive to exceed client expectation<br /></li></ul>__________________________________________________<br /><br />Though we try our best to respond to 